Freeworld Coatings, Petmin May Be Active in Early Trading in Johannesburg

-- B y   C a r l i   L o u r e n s
-- 
2011-07-11T23:01:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-11/freeworld-coatings-petmin-south-african-equity-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or
fall in  South Africa  today. Symbols are in parentheses and
prices are from the last close.  FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index fell 157.31, or 0.5
percent, to 31,845.02 in Johannesburg.  Freeworld Coatings Ltd. (FWD)  : Kansai Paint Co. appealed
a condition imposed by South African antitrust regulators on its
takeover of paint supplier Freeworld. Competition authorities
said in April Kansai must sell the Johannesburg-based company’s
automotive coatings business, Kansai said in an e-mailed
statement today.  Petmin Ltd. (PET)  : Firstrand Bank Ltd. now owns 5.2
percent of the company’s ordinary shares, Petmin said in a
statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Carli Lourens in Johannesburg at 
 clourens@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
John Viljoen at 
 jviljoen@bloomberg.net  